channel.title: One Too Many?
channel.description:
Is it just me, or are there one too many rats in Lumbridge? I do not remember this many rats. There are even more then what is in the photo.
[img]http://i53.tinypic.com/w9v1og.png[/img]

item.title: One Too Many?
item.dc:creator: @Kidpaparoach Kidpaparoach
item.description:
@Kidpaparoach wrote:

[quote=“n10si t, post:21, topic:405029”][quote author=Kidpaparoach link=topic=502039.msg3676364#msg3676364 date=1311273026]

It’s based in the middle ages, people still listened to God and rejected science - of course the living conditions are going to be absolute shit.
[/quote]Really? Over 5 billion people believe in god. Atheism isn’t the majority.

Actually, only 2.3 billion people believe in God. The other 2.7 billion believe in a god. The other 1 billion people don’t.

I’m a muslim… Allah translate as god so you are incorrect. Our version of ‘god’ may differ however it has the same meaning :3.

he was referring the the christian/catholic god[/quote]
True but in my personal opinion he should have stated that, the wording that was used kind of made it feel like religion separates people (which it unfortunately does). If we approach how we talk about religion differently hopefully it can a start to being more accepting of other peoples religions. This mostly doesn’t apply to Christians nowadays (but when it does it can be quite bad) more the Eastern religions (like my own).
Hopefully if we talk about religions in the correct manner there wont be so much tension aka my mum wont be like ‘don’t trust that chinky so much’ -.- one day haha…
